imp(Object, Class<T>) - Static method in class net.cassite.style.Core
Type Conversion.
In order to use Style's type conversion,
the class to be converted to may contain methods like this:
static R from(T o)
OR the class of the object (param 'o') to convert may contain methods like this:
toT
e.g.
The following definition means you can convert String to User or convert User to String.

imp(Object, Class<T>) - Method in interface net.cassite.style.var
Implicit Type Conversion.
To achieve implicit type conversion,
the class to be converted to may contain methods like this:
static R from(T o)
OR the class of the object (param 'o') to convert may contain methods like this:
toT
e.g.
The following definition means you can convert String to User or convert User to String with this method.
